Package models

Class Deck

  • java.lang.Object
    • models.Deck
  • public class Deck
extends java.lang.Object
    This models.Deck class represents a physical deck of 52 playing, with each containing a unique combination of rank and suit. Cards can be drawn from the deck or put back in. Cards are face down when in the deck. The deck also handles the creation of the set of cards that it uses.
    Version:
    2022-02-24
    Author:
    Devon X. Dalrymple

      • insertCardsInInvertedOrder

        public void insertCardsInInvertedOrder​(java.util.List newCards)
        Adds cards to the deck in the inverted order of which they came in. It also places these cards face down. Why: This is necessary to refill the cards from the discard pile into the deck in Patience Solitaire.
        Parameters:
        newCards - The cards to insert to the top of the deck one at a time in order.
